<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12056d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12056d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12056d"> 56(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> spy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les Anglais, dont les repr&eacute;sailles, on le voit, &eacute;taient terribles, usaient des m&ecirc;mes moyens; ils avaient organis&eacute; un service d&apos;espionnes, &laquo;d&apos;espyes&raquo;, comme disent les vieux textes; les hommes aussi &eacute;taient employ&eacute;s &agrave; cette &oelig;uvre r&eacute;pugnante sous le nom de &laquo;messagiers&raquo;. <br><font color="green">[The English, whose reprisals, we see, were terrible, used the same means; they employed a service of <mark>women spies</mark>, &ldquo;d&apos;espyes,&rdquo; as the old texts have it; men were also put to this repugnant work under the name of &ldquo;messagiers&rdquo;.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 144</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
